should give you your public IP address as seen from another location on the internet:

sudo apt-get install curl
curl -4 icanhazip.com
# different check:
curl https://checkip.amazonaws.com

# Network monitoring programs that provide ip(and port) used on server and that reveal from IPs where traffic is comming from:
https://www.binarytides.com/linux-commands-monitor-network/
to name a few featured in the article above:
iptraf, iftop, Nload, tcptrack, Trafshow
